intro: Gonocarpus keigheryi, commonly known as the Keighery's gonocarpus, is a flowering plant native to northern Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae and is characterized by its evergreen, narrow leaves and showy, fragrant flowers. The plant produces small, woody fruits that contain seeds, and it typically grows in sandy or rocky soils. It is well adapted to arid and semi-arid environments, showcasing resilience to drought and heat.
